    • Constructor Detail

      • SeRequest

        public SeRequest(java.nio.ByteBuffer aidToSelect,
                 java.util.List<ApduRequest> apduRequests,
                 boolean keepChannelOpen,
                 SeProtocol protocolFlag,
                 java.util.Set<java.lang.Short> successfulSelectionStatusCodes)
        The constructor called by a ProxyReader in order to open a logical channel, to send a set of APDU commands to a SE application, or both of them.
        • For PO requiring an AID selection, the aidToSelect should be defined with non null value.
        • For PO not supporting AID selection, the aidToSelect should be defined as null. - The protocolFlag parameter is optional.
        Parameters:
        aidToSelect - the aid to select
        apduRequests - the apdu requests
        keepChannelOpen - the keep channel open
        protocolFlag - the expected protocol
        successfulSelectionStatusCodes - a list of successful status codes for the select application command
